# Type Boundaries

## File Roles

| File               | Role                                                                        |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `src/types.ts`     | Shared vocabulary enums only. Pure definitions, zero imports.               |
| `src/index.ts`     | Barrel re-exports + aggregate interfaces (SystemConfig, ScenarioTesting).   |
| Service `types.ts` | Types owned by that service.                                                |
| Parent `types.ts`  | Barrel re-exports plus aggregate service contracts/interfaces where needed. |

## Rules

- Every `types.ts` MUST have a sibling `CLAUDE.md`. No orphaned type files.
- Shared enums (`TopicKey`, `ClassifierIntent`, `EscalationLevel`, `GrocerySection`, `ClarificationReason`, `InputMethod`) live in `src/types.ts` because no single service owns them.
- If an enum is used across the 01↔02 boundary, it belongs in `src/types.ts` — not in a leaf service.
- Leaf types import shared enums from `src/types.ts` as value imports when they are used at runtime and via `import type` only when referenced purely in type positions.
- Legitimate cross-tree imports include the state-service import of `QueueState` from queue (01) and aggregate contract files such as `src/02-supporting-services/types.ts`, which define service interfaces across the 01↔02 boundary.
- `import-x/no-cycle` is enforced by ESLint at `maxDepth: 50`. Circular dependencies are build errors.
